 the vertical; rho is closed; alpha broad with straight bar; sigma has horizontal top and bottom bars, joined by a curving stroke rather than two distinct diagonals; omega sits very slightly above the line, is circular and open with short arms",[379,380],{"type":38,"l":39,"from":40,"to":40,"h":43,"unit":42,"atLeast":43,"atMost":43},{"type":46,"l":47,"from":40,"to":48,"h":49,"unit":42},{"_":382,"notBefore":383,"notAfter":384,"evidence":385},"Dated to the end of the 4th century BCE by the burial goods",-325,-301,"archaeological-context",[387,388],{"_":56,"type":57,"ref":58},{"_":60,"type":61,"ref":62,"offset":63},[390],[66,67],[69,70],{"_":393,"role":76,"ref":394},"Museo Archeologico Santi Furnari di Tripi","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/177",{"_":396,"type":80},"ME23435",{"_":82,"mainLang":83,"languages":398},[82],{"n":87,"url":400,"height":216,"width":217,"desc":218,"surfaceType":92},"ISic004411_tiled.tif",[402],{"atLeast":95,"atMost":95},[348,404,102,405],"Bacci, Coppolino, Sofia, Arizia, 2015, Tripi. Il museo archeologico \"Santi Furnari\". Guida all'esposizione","Sofia, 2018, Nuove iscrizioni funerarie dalla necropoli di Abakainon",[352,407,108,408],"ILQ4RQGU","JQQKI6JP",[410,411,412,15,19,23,113,114,115,116,114,413,119,83],"isic004411","epitaph for kratisstos",{"_":181},"museo archeologico santi furnari di tripi","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>Κρατίσστω \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"author":3,"date":4,"citedRange":416,"ptr":417,"ref":418,"title":2,"citation":5,"uri":6},"113 fig.115",{"target":124},{"_":126,"target":126},{"file":420,"uri":420,"title":421,"status":422,"editionAuthor":13,"type":423,"objectType":424,"material":428,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":429,"handNote":433,"date":438,"places":442,"geo":446,"provenance":56,"provenanceGeo":448,"country":71,"region":72,"settlement":60,"repository":449,"idno":453,"textLang":454,"tmNumber":26,"facsimile":456,"letterHeights":458,"publications":460,"zotero":461,"keywords":462,"html":467,"bibl":468,"citedRangeSort":416,"languageSort":82,"materialSort":23,"typeSort":15},"ISic004417","Epitaph for [-?-], child of Gerontios",{"_":181},{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},{"_":425,"ana":426,"ref":427},"plinth","#object.arch_element.plinth","https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/1910.html",{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},{"layout":430},{"p":431,"rs":432,"damage":26},"Remains of two lines of Greek letters, apparently centred on the face of the plinth; the second line sits directly above the lower moulding",{"_":31,"ana":32,"ref":33},{"lettering":434,"dimensions":435},"Simple, widely spaced letters. Omega is wide and open, with horizontal tails; rho has a large, closed eye; omicron is small and mid-line; nu is regular and with both verticals full length",[436,437],{"type":38,"l":142,"from":40,"to":48,"h":43,"unit":42,"atLeast":43,"atMost":43},{"type":46,"l":47,"from":40,"to":48,"unit":42},{"_":439,"notBefore":440,"notAfter":441,"evidence":385},"The tomb has not been excavated fully, but the cemetery went out of use around the end of the 3rd century BCE or early 2nd century, offering a terminus ante quem",-350,-201,[443,445],{"_":56,"type":57,"ref":58,"corresp":444},"#findspot",{"_":60,"type":61,"ref":62,"offset":63},[447],[66,67],[69,70],{"_":450,"role":451,"ref":452},"Necropoli di Abakainon","site","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/186",{"type":80},{"_":82,"mainLang":83,"languages":455},[82],{"n":87,"url":457,"height":216,"width":217,"desc":218,"surfaceType":92},"ISic004417_tiled.tif",[459],{"atLeast":95,"atMost":95},[348,102,405],[352,108,408],[463,464,465,15,425,23,113,114,115,116,114,466,119,83],"isic004417","epitaph for [-?-], child of gerontios",{"_":181},"necropoli di abakainon","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"a